<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{2}{y}={48}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{8}{y}={6}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{9},{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{2}{y}={48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={48}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{48}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{\left(\frac{{{48}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}\right)}+-{8}{y}={6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{6}}{{-{{4}}}}\cdot{\left({48}\right)}--\frac{{6}}{{-{{4}}}}{\left({2}\right)}{y}+-{8}{y}={6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{72}-{\left(-{3}\right)}{y}+-{8}{y}={6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{y}+{\left(-{8}\right)}{y}={6}-{72}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{y}+{\left(-{8}\right)}{y}=-{66}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3}+{\left(-{8}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{66}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{11}{y}=-{66}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{66}}{{-{{11}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{2}{\left({6}\right)}={48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{\left({12}\right)}={48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={48}-{\left({12}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{36}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{9},{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

